7.30	Titanite	Titanite	Titanite, or sphene (from the Greek sphenos (σφηνώ), meaning wedge), is a calcium titanium nesosilicate mineral, CaTiSiO5. Trace impurities of iron and aluminium are typically present. Also commonly present are rare earth metals including cerium and yttrium; calcium may be partly replaced by thorium.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/00/Titanite_crystals_on_Amphibole_-_Ochtendung%2C_Eifel%2C_Germany.jpg/300px-Titanite_crystals_on_Amphibole_-_Ochtendung%2C_Eifel%2C_Germany.jpg
